b波潜時の増加
increase in the time from the onset of light stimulus to the peak of the b-wave
a波潜時の増加

a波潜時の減少
decrease in the time from onset of stimulus to beginning of the a-wave

視神経乳頭小窩の形態異常

any structural anomaly of either of the two pits that appear bilaterally in the region destined to become the forebrain as the cranial neural folds fuse; these optic pits or sulci continue to deepen laterally and bulge from the two sides of the forebrain to become the optic vesicles
前後軸の重複
partial or complete duplication of rostral-caudal axis structures
吻側身体の切り詰め
rostral part of body truncated; typically with the caudal portion of the body relatively normal
臓側内胚葉の欠如

absence of the primitive endoderm-derived tissue which remains in contact with and surrounds the extra-embryonic ectoderm and the epiblast and provides signals for the differentiation and patterning of the epiblast; a small number of visceral endoderm cells also contribute to the endoderm of the embryonic gut
前方臓側内胚葉の欠如
absence of the extraembryonic tissue that is responsible for the proper orientation of the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo and for appropriate patterning of adjacent embryonic tissue
前方臓側内胚葉の拡張

the extraembryonic tissue that is responsible for the proper orientation of the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo and for appropriate patterning of adjacent embryonic tissue occupies a greater area in the extraembryonic region
遠位臓側内胚葉の欠如
absence of the precursors of the anterior visceral endoderm that arises at the distal tip of the embryo
壁側内胚葉の欠如
absence of the primitive endoderm-derived tissue that lines the luminal surface of the mural trophectoderm
歯胚間葉の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the mesenchyme enclosed by dental organ
結膜杯細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of a goblet cell that is part of the epithelium of the conjunctiva, and is the source of tear mucins which are secreted from it
神経ヒダの欠如
absence of the elevated margins of the neural groove
神経板の欠如
absence of the flat, thickened layer of ectodermal cells in the neuroectodermal area of the embryo's dorsal surface that develops into the neural tube and neural crest

label.value: abnormal epigenetic regulation of gene expression

value.value: エピジェネティックな異常による遺伝子発現調節

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal epigenetic regulation of gene expression

value.value: any anomaly in the process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression, in which the process is mitotically or meiotically heritable, or is stably self-propagated in the cytoplasm of a resting cell, and does not entail a change in DNA sequence
水晶体板の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the paired thickenings of surface ectoderm that become invaginated to form the embryonic lens vesicles
水晶体板の変性
a retrogressive impairment of function or destruction of the paired thickenings of surface ectoderm that normally become invaginated to form the embryonic lens vesicles
水晶体板の欠如
absence of the paired thickenings of surface ectoderm that normally become invaginated to form the embryonic lens vesicles
羊水過少
presence of an abnormally low amniotic fluid volume in the amniotic sac; the opposite of polyhydramnios
羊水成分異常

any alteration in the expected chemical makeup of the watery liquid within the amnion that surrounds and cushions a growing fetus; normally, early in gestation, amniotic fluid is similar to maternal plasma, mainly water with electrolytes, and later in gestation, proteins, carbohydrates, lipids, phospholipids originating from the lungs, fetal cells, and urea are deposited in the fluid
前後軸の短縮
length reduction or truncation of the axis that runs from the head to the tail of the body
平たい頭
the appearance of a flattened surface outline or contour of a normally rounded head of an organism
平たい顔
the appearance of a flattened surface outline or contour of a normally rounded face of an organism
頭部の発生異常
anomaly in the process in which the anatomical structures of the head are generated and organized
頭部の発生遅延
late onset of the induction and/or differentiation of the head
前頭鼻突起の欠如
absence of the unpaired embryonic prominence that is formed by the tissues surrounding the forebrain vesicle and develops into the forehead and bridge of the nose/snout
臓側中胚葉の形態異常
any structural abnormality of the inner layer of lateral plate mesoderm, located above (dorsally) the endoderm, which forms the circulatory system and future gut wall
壁側中胚葉の形態異常
any structural abnormality of the outer layer of lateral plate mesoderm, located under (ventrally) the ectoderm, which forms the future body wall
体節数の増加
increase in the average number of somites formed relative to littermates or other controls
前体節中胚葉の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the unsegmented field of paraxial mesoderm present posterior to the most recently formed somite pair, from which somites will form
沿軸中胚葉のサイズ減少
reduced size or deficiency of the mesoderm lying at either side of the midline embryonic notochord that, on segmentation, forms the paired somites
沿軸中胚葉の欠如
absence or loss of the mesoderm normally found at either side of the midline embryonic notochord that, on segmentation, forms the paired somites.
筋肉前駆細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of cells that will develop into muscle cells
筋肉前駆細胞の生理異常
anomaly in the function of cells that will develop into muscle cells
胚体内体腔の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the part of the coelom in the embryo between the somatopleuric and splanchnopleuric mesoderm; the principal body cavities of the trunk (thoracic, abdominal, and pelvic) arise from this embryonic part of the coelom
制御性T細胞のアポトーシス増加
increase in the number of regulatory T cells undergoing programmed cell death
制御性T細胞のアポトーシス減少
decrease in the number of regulatory T cells undergoing programmed cell death
細胞傷害性T細胞のアポトーシス増加
increase in the number of cytotoxic T cells undergoing programmed cell death
細胞傷害性T細胞のアポトーシス減少
decrease in the number of cytotoxic T cells undergoing programmed cell death
ケラチノサイト遊走異常
anomaly in the movement of keratinocyes or their precursors to the appropriate location in the body
ケラチノサイト遊走増加
increased or faster movement of keratinocyes or their precursors to the appropriate location in the body
ケラチノサイト遊走減少
reduced or slower movement of keratinocyes or their precursors to the appropriate location in the body
神経堤細胞の分化障害

abnormal or arrest of differentiation of the transient and highly migratory group of cells that delaminate in early embryonic development from the dorsal neural tube and give rise to a variety of differentiated cell types
